   "source": [
    "So we will now scrapping the quotes from the website and storing it in a csv file. We will be using the requests library to get the HTML content of the webpage and BeautifulSoup to parse the HTML and extract the quotes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "113f5bca",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Importing Libraries and Connecting to the Website"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d0f18fcb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import requests\n",
    "from bs4 import BeautifulSoup\n",
    "link = 'https://quotes.toscrape.com/'\n",
    "res = requests.get(link)\n",
    "soup = BeautifulSoup(res.text, 'html.parser')"
